-- Platinum hits record on supply, palladium jumps
-- 
-- Sun Feb 3, 2008 7:49pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/04/us-markets-platinum-idUSSP9889420080204

 

 SINGAPORE  (Reuters) - Platinum roared to another record high on Monday as supply concerns in main producer South Africa persisted, lifting sister metal palladium to its best level in six years. 

 Platinum rose to $1,765/1,770 an ounce from $1,752/1,759 an ounce late in New York on Friday. Palladium gained to $412.50/416.50 an ounce from $410.00/413.00 an ounce. (Reporting by Lewa Pardomuan; Editing by  Valerie Lee )